---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="container">

      <section class="hero">
        <h1>About Us</h1>
      </section>

      <section class="about">
        <h2>Why this platform exists</h2>
        <p>
          Mind the Gael exists because female athletes often have limited and inconsistent access to sports psychology support. For many, exposure to mental performance guidance only comes through occasional team psychology sessions or through private access that requires time, money, and opportunity they may not have. This creates a gap where important knowledge about confidence, pressure, focus, and mental wellbeing is not always accessible when athletes need it most. This platform exists to change that. By bringing clear, practical sports psychology content directly to female athletes, so they can build understanding, tools, and confidence in their own time, throughout their sporting journey.
        </p>

        <h2>Problem we’re solving</h2>
        <p>
        There is a gap between traditional sports psychology and the lived experience of female athletes. Most support is either too academic or too generic. Mind the Gael focuses on real sporting environments, helping athletes manage pressure, stay focused, and build confidence in training, matches, and high-pressure moments.
        </p>

        <h2>What will I find here?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Sports psychology explained in a clear, practical way</li>
          <li>Mental performance tools for training and match day</li>
          <li>Insights into focus, confidence, and pressure management</li>
          <li>Understanding of team dynamics and performance under pressure</li>
          <li>Evidence-based concepts translated into real sporting situations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Is this platform for me?</h2>
        <p> The content is for female athletes, coaches, and support staff who want to better understand the mental side of performance.</p>
         <p>It’s for those who want to:</p>
          <ul>
             <li>perform more consistently under pressure</li>
             <li>build confidence in key moments</li>
             <li>want tounderstand what affects mindset, focus, and decision-making in sport</li>
             <li>who are struggling with their mental wellbeing in sport and want to better understand what they are experiencing, why it may be happening, and what steps they can take to support themselves and seek help when needed.</li>
             <li>for anyone working in player development or grassroots coaching who wants a clearer understanding of sports psychology in action.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>

        <h2>Start here</h2>
        <div class="start-buttons">
          <a href="/blog/training-the-mind/" class="start-button">Training the Mind</a>
          <a href="/blog/gael-performance-toolkit/" class="start-button">Gael Performance Toolkit</a>
          <a href="/blog/strong-minds-stronger-players/" class="start-button">Strong Minds, Stronger Players</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  h1 {
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  h2 {
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: #f0cdff;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about p,
  .honest p,
  .what-we-build p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .honest {
    border-left: 3px solid #69005a;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .what-we-build ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .what-we-build ul li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .about ul {
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .closing {
    color: #f0cdff;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .start-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .start-button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.2rem;
    background-color: var(--green-lime);
    color: var(--green-dark);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .start-button:hover {
    background-color: var(--purple-light);
    border-color: var(--purple);
    color: var(--green-dark);
  }
</style>
